Here is the complete code for a simple website. I have combined the HTML, CSS (for styling), and JavaScript (for logic) into a single file for simplicity.

### How to use this:
1.  Open a text editor (like Notepad on Windows or TextEdit on Mac).
2.  Copy the code below and paste it into the editor.
3.  Save the file as **`index.html`**.
4.  Double-click the file to open it in your web browser.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Random Joke Generator</title>
    <style>
        /* CSS: Making the page look nice */
        body {
            font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif;
            background-color: #f0f2f5;
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: center;
            height: 100vh;
            margin: 0;
        }

        .container {
            background-color: white;
            padding: 40px;
            border-radius: 10px;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
            text-align: center;
            max-width: 400px;
            width: 100%;
        }

        h1 {
            color: #333;
        }

        #joke-text {
            font-size: 18px;
            color: #555;
            margin: 20px 0;
            min-height: 60px; /* Keeps the box size stable */
        }

        button {
            background-color: #007bff;
            color: white;
            border: none;
            padding: 12px 24px;
            font-size: 16px;
            border-radius: 5px;
            cursor: pointer;
            transition: background-color 0.3s;
        }

        button:hover {
            background-color: #0056b3;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <div class="container">
        <h1>Joke Generator</h1>
        <p id="joke-text">Click the button to see a joke!</p>
        <button onclick="tellJoke()">Get New Joke</button>
    </div>

    <script>
        // JavaScript: The logic

        // 1. The list of jokes
        const jokes = [
            "Why did the chicken cross the road? To get to the other side!",
            "Why don't skeletons fight each other? They don't have the guts.",
            "I told my doctor I broke my arm in two places. He told me to stop going to those places.",
            "Why do programmers prefer dark mode? Because light attracts bugs."
        ];

        // 2. The function to pick a random joke
        function tellJoke() {
            // Get a random number based on the length of the array
            const randomIndex = Math.floor(Math.random() * jokes.length);

            // Select the joke from the array
            const selectedJoke = jokes[randomIndex];

            // Update the HTML element with the joke
            document.getElementById("joke-text").innerText = selectedJoke;
        }
    </script>

</body>
</html>
```

### How it works:
1.  **HTML:** Creates a box (`div`) containing a heading, a paragraph for the joke text, and a button.
2.  **CSS:** Centers everything on the screen and adds some color to make it look modern.
3.  **JavaScript:**
    *   It stores 4 jokes in an **Array** (a list).
    *   When the button is clicked, it uses `Math.random()` to pick a number between 0 and 3.
    *   It takes the text from that specific spot in the list and puts it into the `<p>` tag on the screen.

